changeFileType

NAME
	changeFileType

SYNOPSIS
	changeFileType TYPE1 TYPE2
	changeFileType [OPTIONS] TYPE1 (TYPE2)?

DESCRIPTION
	This changes the file extension within a directory from TYPE1 to TYPE2. Additionally with various options can instead strip/add extensions from/to TYPE1

OPTIONS
	-h, --help
		Output this help file
	-s, --strip
		Will strip all the files in the directory from TYPE1 to no file extension
	-a, --add
		Will add all the files in the directory from no file extension to TYPE1
	-v, --verbose
		Prints off each change to the terminal
	-r, --recursive
		Will go through each subdirectory of where the program is run and re-run in those subdirectories
